{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_india_ver02/data/sn83045433/100493408/1908030601/0273.xml":{"full_text":"ADVANCE AT OPENING\nStagnation Follows on Small\nProfit-taking Sales.\nNO LIQUIDATION OBSERVABLE\nStreet Strongly Impressed with the\nBelief that the Worst Is Over and\na Return of Prosperity Is in Evi\ndence~Pleased with Bank of Eng\nland's Reduction in Discount Rate.\nNew York, March 5.\u2014 Although during\nthe past fortnight the undertone of the\nstock market has been perceptibly firmer\nand prices have been goverened on the\nwhole by an advancing tendency, specu\nlatjve sentiment is so depressed and\nthe inertia in the stock market so pro\nnounced that gains in market valuations\nhave been mostly in the nature of spurts\neven if on each occasion a considerable\nshare of the gain has been retained.\nThe present character of the market\nwas again exemplified to-day. An upward\nmovement in prices made some headway\nvesterday, and was continued over into\nto-day\u2019's stock exchange session, reen\nforced by the morning's development of\na reduction in the Bank of England's\ndiscount rate; but after this rise had run\na little way it stopped and the market\nrelapsed for the rest of the day into com\nplete stagnation, such changes in prices\nas then occurred being largely as the re\nsult of small profit-taking sales. The net\nconsequence of it all was a mixture of\ntrivial advances and declines in the lead\nIng stocks with the volume of transac\ntions decidedly below that of yesterday.\nStocks Remain Searce.\nThere was no denying, however, that\nthe market again gave proof of the\nradical change that has recently come\nabout in its general temper and situation.\nNo liquidadion is observable, stocks are\nscarce, and it is obvious that commercial,\nmercantile, and manufacturing business\nthroughout the country is mending.\nWhile, therefore, other factors, such as\npolitical matters and the natural work\ning of influences always attending upon\na period of slow recuperation in the\nsecurity market after a disastrous panic\nmay continue to affect values for an\nindefinite further time the consciousness\nis steadily gaining ground in the financial\ndistrict that the worst, both in business\nand the stock market prices, has been\nseen and that from now on things will be\nbetter,\nThe United States Stee] stocks were\nperhaps particular features of strength\nto-day by reason of the undisputed ad\nmission of the improvement now visible\nin the iron and steel business, and be\ncause of the fact that evidence to this\nimprovement can be easily accumulated.\nAdvance in the Northern Pacific shares\nstarted up again the old rumor on the\nfloor of the Stock Exchange of a pos\nsible extra distribution upon the stock.\nCar in Sharp Advance.\nThe American Car and Foundry com\nmon shares rose sharply at the opening\nof business because of the decision of the\ndirectors of the company to continue divi\ndends on the stock at the old rate, despite\nthe company's poor business prospects in\nthe immediate future. The surplus ac\ncumulated by the American Car and\nFoundry Company as the result of the\nexceeding profitable operations of\nprevious years is, however, large.\n\nThe Great Northern Ore certificates\nwere again heavily bought by commis\nsion houses, usually acting for inter\nests identified with the control of the\ncompany, and the current explanation\nfor the movement was that the dividend\ndistribution upon the certificates was\nlikely to be increased.\nThe Bank of England's reduction of its\ndiscount rate to 3% per cent was neces\nsarily pleasing, although the matter had\nbeen pretiy well anticipated, because it\nis the lowest discount rate of the bank\nseen at any time since September, 1906,\nand the lowest recorded at this rate since\n1905. The underlying cause of this action\nis, of course, the slackening of business\nin England, which has been felt there\nno less than in the United States, and the\nevent strongly indicates that our coun\ntry will keep within its borders in the\npresent year, or at least for many months\nto come, the gold received from Europe\nin jast year's troubles.\n\nNew York, March 5.\u2014Money on call at the stock\nexchange to-day opened at 2 per cent: highest, 2:\nlowest, 1%; closing, 2. Most of the loans were at 2.\nTime money was not especially active. It was\nobtainable with moderate liberality. Rates, 3'%$a3%\nper cent for sixty days; 3%ad for ninety days; #a\nA% for four, five, and six months; 5a5% for a year.\nMercantile paper was in somewhat improved de\nmand, but buyers were still insistent on full rates.\nA fairly large assortment was offered. Rates 5%\nto per cent for sixty days and ninety days, in\ndorsed bills receivable; 5% to 6 for chbice four to\nsix months single names; 6% for others.\nThe market for sterling to-day closed heaty with\nsight bills 3x below yesterday. Rates for actual\nbusiness were as follows: Sixty days, 4.8355a4.8360;\ndemand, 4.8650a4 8655: cables, 4.8685a4 8600: commer\ncial bills, 4.82%ad.83%. The supply of cotton bills\nVAS Saree\nt\n\nSt. Ives*\ni Silver Pick\u00ae A\nTy LR NE HR AO RR\nGOVERNMENT BOUNDS.\nAtlanta\u201d\nNew York, March 5.--Closing quotations of United\nStates government bonds:\nPiamondfleld Black Butte\u00ae................. 19\nTriangle\u00ae nr sm a aA 8\nBid. Asked.\nregistered, IB30.......ccouiii nina 104 104%\n23, COMPAR 20s s nen seonsesnsnveksss FY Ie\n3s, registered. AHIR. .o.uuscencnessnsisiancs 10 102\n35, oonpom, THB... cvseusiriiins srs nniiainn 101 102\nJs, small Bees snsrerssrrsnisinnsvnsrin sanne 100%\n15, COMPONL Tr viv sah essriuin te sunse snonn rams 122%\nTramps Consolidated\u00ae................ Wh 19\nGo Id Bar* assess tbssbachassibtasaisbantontins 6\n{Tim Butler\u00ae......covriiiininniinniae, 3\nCRONIN BOBDRBIR. \u00aboon cei nnnnsrpsnsnmnensmms 5\nFRHDPAIRRI\u2122 (ans. suavesnvarnssannsnsnnsian sensssn 10\nRoanoke\u00ae .............ccosssisisnssnnsnsnsnnn 7\nSawtooth Galena\nTREASURY STA